title: Nicole Kidman | Fox News
description: Nicole Kidman is an Australian accent who has starred in major blockbuster hits including "Moulin Rouge!," "Eyes Wide Shut" and "To Die For." She is married to country singer Keith Urban and was previously wed to actor Tom Cruise.

Answer: Nicole Kidman is an actress and producer known for her leading roles in several award-winning films and television productions over the last three decades. Kidman's long-time career and growing list of accolades have made her one of the highest-paid actresses in Hollywood.
Moreover, she is an Australian citizen, and many of her breakout films in the 1980s were filmed there. Kidman has received six Golden Globe Awards, two Primetime Emmy Awards and an Academy Award.
For the next decade, Kidman continued building a name for herself on the big screen with leading roles in 1992's "Far and Away," 1995's "Batman Forever," "To Die For," the 1998 film “Practical Magic” and Stanley Kubrick's last film in 1999, "Eyes Wide Shut." However, Kidman did not start receiving Academy recognition for her films until later in her career, with nominations for the 2001 musical "Moulin Rouge!," 2010's "Rabbit Hole," 2016's "Lion" and "Being the Ricardos" in 2021.
She has received numerous Emmy Awards and received a lead role in television shows such as "Hemingway & Gellhorn," "Big Little Lies," "Top of the Lake: China Girl," "The Undoing” and "Nine Perfect Strangers." She received outstanding lead actress and outstanding limited series Emmy Awards as an executive producer and actress on "Big Little Lies."
In 2024, movies and TV shows starring Kidman included “A Family Affair," “Babygirl,” “The Perfect Couple” and “Lioness.” In 2025, Kidman starred in the movie “Holland.”

Answer: Nicole Kidman was married to fellow actor Tom Cruise throughout the ‘90s. They met on the set of “Days of Thunder” in 1990 and were quickly married. The couple starred in other movies together, including “Far and Away” and “Eyes Wide Shut.” In February 2001, Kidman and Cruise announced their split.
 After her split from Cruise, she dated musician Lenny Kravitz. During an interview in 2017, while promoting her TV series “Big Little Lies,” also starring Kravitz’s daughter, Zoë, she spoke about briefly being engaged to Kravitz.
 In 2005, Kidman met Keith Urban, and the two were engaged the following year. In June 2006, they were married. In September 2025, Kidman and Urban split.

Answer: Nicole Kidman has four children. During her marriage to Tom Cruise, they adopted two children together, Isabella and Connor.
 While she was married to Keith Urban, the pair welcomed two biological children, Sunday Rose and Faith Margaret. Amid their divorce, Kidman asked to be the primary residential parent of their daughters.

Answer: Nicole Kidman filed for divorce from Keith Urban on September 30, 2025. They were married for 19 years.
 Sources close to the couple have labeled the divorce as “inevitable,” even though it came as a shock to the public. "It really hasn’t been a secret," a source told People, adding they "have been living separately for a while now." Kidman cited “irreconcilable differences” and “marital difficulties” as the reasons for the split, according to documents obtained by Fox News Digital.
